translations.issuesTool.faqs.a9: Please submit time-sensitive issues as soon as possible so that a team member can look at it while the game is in progress. For large games that are high-priority and have large fan impact, mark it as critical so that someone will look at it immediately.
translations.issuesTool.faqs.a6:
'Open' = No work has started on the issue.

'Validated' = The issue has been reviewed, and teams have confirmed the issue is correctly categorized and reproducible.

'In progress' = Someone is actively looking into the issue.

'Code Review' = A fix has been submitted and is awaiting approval.

'In QA' = A fix has been deployed for validation in a test environment.

'Ready for Prod' = Changes have been approved and the fix is ready for deployment.

'Closed' = The issue is resolved.
translations.issuesTool.faqs.a7: Follow the linked ticket to see the progress on work being done there.
translations.issuesTool.faqs.a4:
Visit the MY ISSUES page to view all tickets you have created in the Issues Tool

Any user with a JIRA account will also receive notification updates via email. Not sure if you have an account? Visit https://jira.disney.com and log in with your MyID account.
translations.issuesTool.faqs.a5: You can communicate that in the description of the ticket - when a ticket comes in, our team will read it. If you have a due date, we will do our best to meet that and communicate what's doable on our end. Feel free to comment in the ticket directly to ask about an expected timeline.
translations.issuesTool.faqs.a2: You can use the search function on the issues tool for keywords to see if someone else has already reported your issue and what the status of that ticket is.
translations.issuesTool.faqs.a3:
Response times are based on the severity level of your issue.

Response Time for Guest Facing Products and Tools

Sev 1/2 (Critical) issues will page the on-call engineer who should respond within 15 minutes.

Sev 3 (Major) issues should be addressed within 2 business days.

Sev 4 (Minor) issues will be addressed as time permits, but can take several weeks.

Response Time for Enterprise Products

[EP SLA]

* If you need immediate assistance, update your ticket in the Issue Details view to Sev 1/2 (Critical).
translations.issuesTool.faqs.a1:
The more details the better! Please include the url of the page that an issue is happening, screenshots of the problem occurring, and any steps one might need to reproduce the error. We have to be able to reproduce the issue on our end in order to fix it, so the more information the better (even browser type, device type, if you're logged in/out of the site, etc.)

For example: https://issues.dtci.technology/issuedetails/CTOI-37439

translations.bpi.projections.note.extend: The College Basketball Power Index (BPI) is a measure of team strength that is meant to be the best predictor of performance going forward. BPI represents how many points above or below average a team is. Strength of Record (SOR) is a measure of team accomplishment based on how difficult a team's W-L record is to achieve. Game predictions account for opponent strength, pace of play, site, travel distance, day's rest and altitude, and are used to simulate the season 10,000 times to produce season projections. Numbers update daily.

The values are adjusted for strength of schedule and down-weighted for "garbage time" (based on win probability). The scale goes from 0 to 100; higher numbers are better and the average is roughly 50 for all categories. Efficiencies update daily during the season. FPI data from seasons prior to 2019 may not be complete.
